  <p class="chiploop-intro"><strong>About ChipLoop:</strong> ChipLoop is an all-in-one agentic AI platform for silicon development. It helps engineers and small teams define, configure, and run connected chip workflows across RTL, verification, implementation, firmware/software, validation, dashboards, and product journeys. Explore ChipLoop at <a href="https://www.getchiploop.com/">https://www.getchiploop.com/</a>.</p>

  <h2>1. Lost engineering context</h2>
  <p>Specs, RTL, logs, reports, and review notes often live in separate places. ChipLoop keeps run-centered evidence attached to the workflow.</p>

  <h2>2. AI output without accountability</h2>
  <p>Generated RTL or scripts may look useful, but they still need checks. ChipLoop connects generation to verification, synthesis, dashboards, and review.</p>

  <h2>3. Manual handoffs between loops</h2>
  <p>Teams often rebuild context when moving between architecture, RTL, verification, implementation, and validation. ChipLoop product journeys carry context forward.</p>

  <h2>4. Hard-to-review EDA output</h2>
  <p>Reports are verbose and scattered. Dashboards plus Ask This Run make failures and next steps easier to inspect.</p>

  <h2>5. Startup tools are hard to adopt</h2>
  <p>Useful tools struggle to enter real workflows. ChipLoop can package tools as agents, apps, workflow stages, or product journeys.</p>

