  <h2>The review problem</h2>
  <p>After a run completes, engineers often need to inspect many files: logs, reports, summaries, generated RTL, constraints, dashboards, and ZIPs. The information exists, but it takes time to find and understand.</p>

  <h2>Ask the run, not a generic chatbot</h2>
  <p>Ask This Run is tied to a specific workflow run. It answers questions using available run context. That makes it different from a general chat tool.</p>
  <p>Useful questions include: What failed? What was generated? What should I inspect first? Are there missing outputs? Is this ready for handoff?</p>

  <h2>Why it changes review</h2>
  <p>Ask This Run makes the run itself more usable. It turns logs and artifacts into an interactive review surface. With Smart Context, it can also prioritize the most relevant evidence before answering.</p>

